The API-Server can be configured via a config file (YAML, JSON or TOML) located at /etc/enclave/config.yaml, $HOME/.enclave or ./. The configuration file supports the following options: Option Allowed Values Description human_readable_output true / false Enable Human-reable output (= to stdout and in color) for the logs log_level debug, info, warn or error Set the log-level production_environment true / false Operate (gin) server in production mode port <port> Port to run the API-Server on
POST /rbac/endpoint Assign an endpoint to a specific resource group.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 404 500 Endpoint assigned to resource group successfully or was already assigned. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/user Assign role to a specific user.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 404 500 Role assigned to user successfully or role was already assigned. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
HEAD /rbac/resource-group Check if a specific resource group exists in the system.
Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 Resource group exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. Resource group does not exist. Internal server error.
HEAD /rbac/role Check if a specific role exists in the system.
Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 Role exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. Role does not exist. Internal server error.
HEAD /users/user Check if a specific user exists.
Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 User exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. User does not exist. Internal server error.
POST /rbac/policy Create a new role-based access control (RBAC) policy.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 404 500 RBAC policy created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. One or more fields were invalid. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/resource-group Create a new resource group.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 409 500 Resource group created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. A resource group with the given name already exists. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/role Create a new role in the system.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 409 500 Role created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. A role with the given name already exists. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.

Responses​ 201 400 401 403 409 500 User created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. A user with the given name already exists. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
DELETE /rbac/policy Delete an existing role-based access control (RBAC) policy, if it existed.

Responses​ 200 400 401 403 500 RBAC policy deleted successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
DELETE /rbac/resource-group Delete an existing resource group.

Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 Resource group deleted successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
DELETE /rbac/role Delete role from the system.

Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 409 500 Roles deleted successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. The resource group could not be deleted due to internal restrictions. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.

Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 User deleted successfully. Returns the deleted user. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.

GET /rbac/role Retrieve a list of users assigned to a specific role.

Responses​ 200 400 401 403 404 500 Successful response with a list of users assigned to the role. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
GET /rbac/resource-group Retrieve a list of endpoints assigned to a specific resource group.

GET /rbac/endpoint Retrieve the resource group assigned to a specific endpoint.

documents.t: Responses​ 200 400 401 403 500 Successful response with the resource group assigned to the endpoint. Empty array if endpoint is not assigned to any resource group. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
